  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2293",
  "title": "Unpredictable range slider behaviour on mobile devices",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nReport a bug.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behaviour?**\r\nThe upper bound handle of the range slider widget is unpredictable and/or intermittently unresponsive on mobile devices. The lower bound handle appears to be unaffected.\r\n\r\nExample available via [this fiddle](https://jsfiddle.net/gsenior/bLjtmzku/1/).\r\n\r\nAlso, when utilising multiple range sliders, the upper bound handle of slider A can occasionally be moved by the lower bound handle of slider B.\r\n\r\n![slider-issue](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/768967/29617623-5c2cda32-880d-11e7-9628-ec830183179d.gif)\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\nWe have reproduced the issue on the following:\r\n\r\n- Chrome v60 on Android 7.1.2\r\n- Safari on iOS 10.3.3 \r\n- Chrome v60 on iOS 10.3.3\r\n\r\nIt can also be replicated on desktop Chrome (v60) by using the Developer Tools -> Device Toolbar -> (e.g. Nexus 5X).\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the proposed solution?**\r\nAfter a bit of hunting around, I _think_ this is related to Preact, Rheostat and event handling. I've created my own build of instantsearch.js, swapping out Preact for React and the issue is resolved. \r\n\r\nI wonder if it is related this bug - https://github.com/iam4x/preact-key0-repro-bug?\r\n",
